tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Shot a final-round 68 at the United Investment Real Estate Wuhan Open to T12 in May at Wuhan Yishan GC. 

2014: Began his PGA TOUR China Series career by missing the cut at the Mission Hills Haikou Open…Finished T29 in his next start, at the Buick Open in Guangzhou…Added a T43 at the Lanhai Open in early June…Had his best outing a week later, turning in a T19 performance, thanks, to a 70-70-67 finish over his final 54 holes at the Earls Beijing Open…Opened 68-71-70 at the OneAsia Tour's Nanshan China Masters and was 4-under entering the final round. Shot a 2-over 73 on the final day during blustery conditions at Nanshan International GC but was still able to record a solo-fourth performance. 
2013: Failed to earn an invitation to the Volvo China Open, shooting rounds of 76-69 in open-qualifying. 
2012: Finished T41 with fellow countrymen Wu Weihuang and Su Dong, along with Australia's Anthony Summers, at the Nanshan China Masters in mid-October…A month later, at the Emirates Australian Open, was one of two Chinese players (Liang Wen-Chong was the other) to make the cut. Went on to T67 at The Lakes GC.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the PGA Tour China Serie was T12th in 2015 at the United Investment Real Estate Wuhan Open.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks 91st in Scoring Average (Actual) on the PGA Tour China Series.
